[[File:Meister Bertram von Minden - Grabow Altarpiece - WGA14309.jpg|thumbnail|right|500px|[[Master Bertram]], Grabow Altarpiece, 1379-1383]] The '''Grabow Altarpiece''' (also known as the '''Petri Altar''') was painted by [[Master Bertram]] around 1379-1383. Originally located in [[St. Petri, Hamburg|St. Petri church]], it is now in the [[Kunsthalle Hamburg|Hamburger Kunsthalle]] in [[Hamburg]], Germany.<ref>''Gothic Art'' by Victoria Charles and Klaus H. Carl 2008 {{ISBN|1844844617}} page 96</ref>
It includes the earliest known depiction of the [[Rest on the Flight into Egypt]] (lower row, last section on the right).<ref>Schiller, Gertud, ''Iconography of Christian Art, Vol. I'', p. 122, 1971 (English trans from German), Lund Humphries, London, {{ISBN|0853312702}}</ref>
