[[File:Sandra-moreschiBW.jpg|thumb|Sandra Moreschi in a photographic portrait]]
'''Sandra Moreschi''' (born December 7, 1946) is an Italian designer of [[Jewish ceremonial art]].

Since the end of the 1980s, Sandra Moreschi has been combining symbols of the Jewish tradition with contemporary design. From 1990 to 2016 she managed a store, Saray, located in the heart of the [[Roman Ghetto]] in via [[Porticus Octaviae|Portico d'Ottavia]]. During this time, she collaborated with Italian artisan shops, among them the Bottega Gatti of [[Faenza]]. Her works are present in important private, museum and institutional collections.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Brockman|first1=Elin Schoen|title=The Jewish Traveler: Rome|url=http://www.hadassahmagazine.org/2010/08/17/jewish-traveler-rome/|website=Hadassah Magazine|date=Aug 2010}}</ref>

